<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>QUOTE OF THE DAY</b></font><br>

<font size="2">"Let us build on the richness of Afghanistan's past, let us
build a new history that will protect and ennoble usall." <br>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/international/asia/21AID.html?todaysheadlines">COLIN L. POWELL,</a>secretary of state.


<hr size="1">



<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>NATIONAL</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/national/21PRIS.html?todaysheadlines">Tight Budgets Force States to Reconsider Crime and Penalties</a></b><br>
After decades of building more prisons and passing tougher sentencing laws, states are being forced by budget deficits to close some prisons and consider shortening sentences.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/national/21FLOR.html?todaysheadlines">Bad Times? Not in a Thriving Florida Town</a></b><br>
If there is one place in the country that is escaping the current recession, it may the city of Port St. Lucie, Fla.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/politics/21ELDE.html?todaysheadlines">Key Players in Budget War: They're Older and They Vote</a></b><br>
The political war over the budget will revolve, in part, around the interests and apprehensions of one extraordinarily powerful group: older Americans.
<P>
</font>













<p>
