<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>POLITICS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/politics/21ELDE.html?todaysheadlines">Key Players in Budget War: They're Older and They Vote</a></b><br>
The political war over the budget will revolve, in part, around the interests and apprehensions of one extraordinarily powerful group: older Americans.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/national/21POLS.html?todaysheadlines">Lieberman Feels the Sting of Criticism Over Enron</a></b><br>
Senator Joseph Lieberman, the Connecticut Democrat, has been buffeted with criticism from both sides of the aisle for his stewardship of one of 10 Congressional committees now investigating Enron.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/national/21DALL.html?todaysheadlines">Ex-Reporter and Civic Leader in Runoff to Be Mayor of Dallas</a></b><br>
Dallas voters have forced a runoff mayoral election between a former journalist with a confrontational style and a civic leader.
<P>
</font>













<p>
