<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>ARTS</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/movies/21GLOB.html?todaysheadlines">'A Beautiful Mind' Wins Four Golden Globes</a></b><br>
Ron Howard's emotional thriller about a brilliant but schizophrenic mathematician won best dramatic picture at the Golden Globe Awards. Russell Crowe, right, won best actor for his work in the film.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/arts/design/21ANTI.html?todaysheadlines">Multifaceted Antiques Show Only Burnished by Adversity</a></b><br>
The 48th  Annual Winter Antiques Show, thrown into disarray by an unplanned relocation to the New York Hilton,  prevailed with handsome booths and superb selections.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/arts/television/21JAME.html?todaysheadlines">Crime and Race in England, Both Factual and Fictitious</a></b><br>
"Materpiece Theater" will present two daring, engrossing films: "The Murder of Stephen Lawrence" and an "Othello" based in  the loosest way on Shakespeare.
<P>
</font>













<p>
<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/pages/arts/index.html?todaysheadline">MORE ARTS NEWS</a>
