<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>NY REGION</b></font><br>




<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/nyregion/21SITE.html?todaysheadlines">Ground Zero Cleanup Defies How Jobs Are Usually Done</a></b><br>
Those removing the rubble at ground zero are trumpeting nothing short of a construction   miracle, and with it, no small victory over cynicism about what labor can get done.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/nyregion/21RADI.html?todaysheadlines">In Shadow of Reactors, Parents Seek Peace of Mind in a Pill</a></b><br>
What's the new suburban drug of choice? Potassium iodide, to ward off radiation from a nuclear power plant meltdown.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2002/01/21/nyregion/21BROO.html?todaysheadlines">Giant Brookhaven Roiled by Battle to Create Town Council Districts</a></b><br>
Just about everything in the Town of Brookhaven is jumbo size, including the latest battle  over how to run it.
<P>
</font>













<p>
